nkine/">Reverse formula and conversion (Celsius to Rankine)</a></p>
	<h3>Rankine</h3>
	<p>The Rankine scale is named after Scottish physicist <b>William John Mac=
quorn Rankine</b>. Similarly to kelvin <b>absolute zero is 0 =C2=B0R</b>, e=
quivalent to -459.67 =C2=B0F. Rankine uses the same interval as Fahrenheit.=
</p>
=09
	<h3>Celsius</h3>
	<p>The Celsius scale is the most commonly used temperature scale and the s=
tandard used for most applications by the scientific community worldwide. T=
he <b>boiling point of water is 100 =C2=B0C</b>. The <b>freezing point is 0=
 =C2=B0C</b>. The word <b>centigrade</b> is used in many languages to descr=
ibe Celsius.</p>
